            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>AudioXplorer 1.4.1</h2>
                <p>Bug fix release.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Real-time capture now works in the installed app.</b> The 1.4 release build was signed without the <code>com.apple.security.device.audio-input</code> entitlement, so macOS silently refused to prompt for microphone access — the real-time window opened but recorded silence.</li>
                    <li><b>Enable toggle in the real-time window no longer gets stuck on.</b> A type-truncation bug made <code>isRecording</code> always report <code>YES</code> after pause, so the toggle kept flipping itself back to ON.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><i>If you previously installed 1.4 and granted microphone access, you may need to remove and re-add AudioXplorer in System Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Microphone — the new build's signature differs from 1.4's.</i></p>
            ]]></description>
